{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"vegetable peeler, peeler, airtight jars, refrigerator","id":"r68844","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-8TtUBm61uto\/XZWYhM1CR_I\/AAAAAAAAd_Y\/6ktfpjNHpmsgOfZDqqaxXzQ5D5Arzps6ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_CZsZtc7oYwvSPDmy.png","title":"Citrus marmalade","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"1300 g citrus fruit of choice (e.g. limes, oranges, cumquats, lemons, grapefruit)"},{"content":"300 g water"},{"content":"600 g sugar, adjust to taste"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"0.3 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 20 gram","carbohydrates":"14 g","calories":"245 kJ \/ 58 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Using a vegetable peeler, remove citrus zest taking care not to include white pith. Place citrus zest into mixing bowl and grate <b>3-5 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add water and cook <b>4 min\/100°C\/\/speed 2<b>. Drain zest through simmering basket and discard water. Place citrus zest back into mixing bowl."},{"content":"Remove white pith from citrus flesh, cut flesh into quarters and remove pips. Add citrus flesh and sugar into mixing bowl. Cook <b>15 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid."},{"content":"Leave simmering basket instead of measuring cup on mixing bowl lid and cook <b>60-80 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Test to see if your marmalade has set (see tips). If not, cook for a further <b>2-3 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid."},{"content":"Transfer marmalade into warmed airtight jars to store. Allow to cool completely then, place in refrigerator until ready to use."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Citrus marmalade is ideal for breakfast any day of the week.","This recipe makes approx. 1000 g of marmalade. Transferred into airtight storage jars, it will make ideal gifts for family and friends.","Reduce temperature to 90°C halfway through cooking time if marmalade begins to bubble onto mixing bowl lid.","Adjust sugar content according to the tartness of your fruit and your personal taste preference.","<strong>Setting point test<\/strong>: place a saucer into the freezer (5-10 minutes). Place 1 tsp marmalade onto the chilled saucer. When marmalade on saucer is cool, push it with your finger. If the marmalade wrinkles, it is ready. If not, cook marmalade for a further 2 minutes then test again.","For a different texture to your marmalade, you may want to julienne (finely slice) your citrus zest instead of grating in step 1.","If a thicker consistency is desired, use jam setter or natural pectin obtainable from health food stores."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 20m","1 litre"]}